# Universe Data Reference

## Source File

`data/universe_master.json` — 7,623 stock records, each with ~100 fields.

## Key Fields (JSON keys → Python aliases)

### Categorical
| JSON Key       | Python field     | Example values                          |
|---------------|------------------|-----------------------------------------|
| Country       | country          | United States, Japan, United Kingdom    |
| Industry      | industry         | Technology, Healthcare, Energy          |
| Sub-Industry  | sub_industry     | Software & IT Services, Banking         |
| Currency      | currency         | USD, EUR, JPY, GBP                      |
| Exchange      | exchange         | NYSE, Nasdaq, Tokyo SE, London SE       |

### Fundamentals
Price, Market_Cap, Pe_Ratio, Pb_Ratio, Dividend_Yield, Earnings_Per_Share, Return_On_Equity, Turnover_By_Value

### Time-Series Metrics (suffixed with period)
Periods: `_1M`, `_3M`, `_6M`, `_1Y`, `_3Y`, `_5Y`, `_10Y`, `_MTD`, `_QTD`, `_YTD`

Metric families: Return, Volatility, Sharpe, Sortino, Skewness, Kurtosis, Max_Drawdown, VaR

## UniverseFilters Coverage

The `UniverseFilters` Pydantic model currently covers a subset of the above. When adding new filter fields:
1. Add to `UniverseFilters` in `backend/models/schemas.py`
2. Add to the `SYSTEM_PROMPT` in `backend/services/agent.py`
3. Add to `_LABEL_MAP` in `agent.py` for the human-readable summary
4. Add to `_build_json_schema()` in `agent.py` (for documentation)
5. Update `backend/docs/sample_chat_responses.json` with an example
